Currently there is no mechanism to resume a previously spawned thread. The send tool (or equivalent) should accept an existing thread/session ID to continue a prior conversation rather than always spawning a fresh agent.

This mirrors opencode's session_id parameter on the task tool â€” pass a prior session_id to resume the same subagent session for multi-turn interactions.

Acceptance criteria:
- send tool (or spawn tool) accepts an optional thread_id / session_id parameter
- If provided and the session exists, the new message is appended to the existing thread and execution resumes
- If provided and the session does not exist, return a clear error (do not silently create a new session)
- If omitted, behaviour is unchanged (new thread spawned)
- The thread's output (e.g. from a prior await) should be accessible after resuming
- Tests covering: resume existing, resume non-existent, resume completed, multi-turn interaction